  "2026-04-07T18:14:15.301Z",codex-agent,"2026-04-07 scope extension: implement create-time --comment plain-text shorthand parity so pm create accepts simple comment text like pm comments --add while retaining deterministic structured key=value parsing and punctuation-safe guidance. Planned files: src/cli/commands/create.ts (+ shared parse helper only if required), tests/unit/create-command.spec.ts, README/PRD/ARCHITECTURE/CHANGELOG."
  "2026-04-07T18:24:04.211Z",codex-agent,"Implementation progress: create --comment now accepts plain-text shorthand by defaulting to a comment seed when structured parsing fails or when single-key colon text is provided (while preserving strict rejection for ambiguous comma key-like fragments such as text=...,scope:...). Added regression coverage in tests/unit/create-command.spec.ts for plain text and colon shorthand plus existing ambiguity guards."
  "2026-04-25T16:54:40.806Z",codex-agent,"Dogfood finding (2026-04-25): comments/notes/learnings --add payloads passed as single CSV-like strings can be interpreted as plain text entries, which is easy to misread as structured parsing. Review parser/doc ergonomics and add explicit examples for unambiguous structured input."
