body: "Delivery feature under the comments UX hardening epic.\n\n## Detailed implementation plan\n1. Command UX wiring\n   - Update comments command signature to accept optional positional text argument in addition to --add.\n   - Allow --author optional value so bare --author falls back to PM_AUTHOR/settings/defaults instead of failing parse.\n   - Add deterministic conflict handling when both positional text and --add are provided in one invocation.\n2. Runtime behavior and compatibility\n   - Preserve existing --add plain text, text=<value>, markdown text:, and stdin token - support.\n   - Keep list mode behavior unchanged when neither positional text nor --add is provided.\n3. Regression coverage\n   - Add integration assertions for positional shorthand success.\n   - Add coverage for conflict path and optional --author path using CLI invocation tests.\n   - Keep help/runtime contract tests passing with updated command usage.\n4. Documentation updates\n   - Update README, PRD, AGENTS examples to show shorthand plus backward-compatible --add usage.\n   - Update CHANGELOG Unreleased notes with compatibility-safe UX improvement.\n5. Verification and closure\n   - Run targeted tests, then full sandbox-safe test and coverage sweeps.\n   - Record verification evidence in linked pm items and close/release epic-feature-task chain."
